<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="298"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                         Trace Selection Strategies</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="299"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="300"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00301" /><CodeLine lineNumber="301"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A trace selection strategy is implemented as a sub-class of Ensemble. The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00302" /><CodeLine lineNumber="302"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// trace through a block B is computed by two DFS traversals of the CFG</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00303" /><CodeLine lineNumber="303"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// starting from B. One upwards, and one downwards. During the upwards DFS,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00304" /><CodeLine lineNumber="304"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// pickTracePred() is called on the post-ordered blocks. During the downwards</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00305" /><CodeLine lineNumber="305"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// DFS, pickTraceSucc() is called in a post-order.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00306" /><CodeLine lineNumber="306"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00307" /><CodeLine lineNumber="307"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00308" /><CodeLine lineNumber="308"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// We never allow traces that leave loops, but we do allow traces to enter</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00309" /><CodeLine lineNumber="309"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// nested loops. We also never allow traces to contain back-edges.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00310" /><CodeLine lineNumber="310"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00311" /><CodeLine lineNumber="311"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This means that a loop header can never appear above the center block of a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00312" /><CodeLine lineNumber="312"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// trace, except as the trace head. Below the center block, loop exiting edges</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00313" /><CodeLine lineNumber="313"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// are banned.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00314" /><CodeLine lineNumber="314"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Return true if an edge from the From loop to the To loop is leaving a loop.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Either of To and From can be null.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317" lineLink="#a845058902483d2afbab93214dcce8684"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="#a845058902483d2afbab93214dcce8684">isExitingLoop</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineloop">MachineLoop</a> &#42;From, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineloop">MachineLoop</a> &#42;To) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> From &amp;&amp; !From-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/loopbase/#a04337b572d34ea413c35dbac5d75530b">contains</a>(To);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// MinInstrCountEnsemble - Pick the trace that executes the least number of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instructions.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00668" /><CodeLine lineNumber="668"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// are ready.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00669" /><CodeLine lineNumber="669"></CodeLine>
